werShell\\\\\\\\v1.0\\\\\\\\powershell.exe\\\" -Command 'Get-Content .flowset/eval-results/WI-010-codex-schema.json'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\r\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_36\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Windows\\\\\\\\System32\\\\\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\\\\\v1.0\\\\\\\\powershell.exe\\\" -Command 'Get-Content .flowset/eval-results/WI-010-perf.codex.json'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"{\\\"reviewer\\\":\\\"codex\\\",\\\"schemaVersion\\\":1,\\\"scores\\\":null,\\\"weightedTotal\\\":null,\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"FAIL\\\",\\\"issues\\\":[{\\\"severity\\\":\\\"P2\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"src/stores/space-store.ts:89\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"`loadMore` sets `isLoadingMore: true` and increments `_reqId`, but if a filter change or `fetchSpaces` invalidates that request before it resolves, the stale `loadMore` finally block skips clearing `isLoadingMore` because `_reqId` no longer matches. The stale data append is blocked, but the loading-more flag can remain true, so a subsequent filtered result with `hasMore: true` renders the \\\\\\\"??ë³´ê¸°\\\\\\\" button permanently disabled. The new race test verifies the stale append is ignored but does not assert `isLoadingMore` is reset.\\\",\\\"recommendation\\\":\\\"Clear pagination state when starting a full reload/filter change, or use separate request tokens/loading flags for `fetchSpaces` and `loadMore` so invalidated load-more requests still release `isLoadingMore`. Add a regression test where the replacement filter response has `hasMore: true` and assert `isLoadingMore === false`.\\\",\\\"defer\\\":false,\\\"deferRationale\\\":null,\\\"fixNow\\\":true},{\\\"severity\\\":\\\"P3\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"prisma/schema.prisma:153\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"The API now caps response size, but the global super-admin path still queries `where status = ACTIVE` ordered by `updatedAt desc, id desc` without a matching composite index. With many ACTIVE spaces, the database may still scan/sort a large candidate set for every page, so the original scale debt is only partially addressed at the query-plan level.\\\",\\\"recommendation\\\":\\\"Plan a migration for an index matching the hot order/filter, e.g. status plus `updatedAt`/`id` ordering, and validate with the target database's query plan. Consider owner/member scoped access patterns separately before choosing indexes.\\\",\\\"defer\\\":true,\\\"deferRationale\\\":\\\"This requires a database schema migration and query-plan validation beyond the read-only pagination patch; response-size correctness is still improved by the current change.\\\",\\\"fixNow\\\":false}]}\\r\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\r\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_38\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Windows\\\\\\\\System32\\\\\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\\\\\v1.0\\\\\\\\powershell.exe\\\" -Command 'Get-Content .flowset/eval-results/WI-010-codex-schema.json'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"{\\r\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\r\\n  \\\"additionalProperties\\\": false,\\r\\n  \\\"required\\\": [\\\"reviewer\\\", \\\"schemaVersion\\\", \\\"scores\\\", \\\"weightedTotal\\\", \\\"verdict\\\", \\\"issues\\\"],\\r\\n  \\\"properties\\\": {\\r\\n    \\\"reviewer\\\": { \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"enum\\\": [\\\"codex\\\"] },\\r\\n    \\\"schemaVersion\\\": { \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\", \\\"enum\\\": [1] },\\r\\n    \\\"scores\\\": { \\\"type\\\": \\\"null\\\" },\\r\\n    \\\"weightedTotal\\\": { \\\"type\\\": \\\"null\\\" },\\r\\n    \\\"verdict\\\": { \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"enum\\\": [\\\"PASS\\\", \\\"WARNING\\\", \\\"FAIL\\\"] },\\r\\n    \\\"issues\\\": {\\r\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"items\\\": {\\r\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\r\\n        \\\"additionalProperties\\\": false,\\r\\n        \\\"required\\\": [\\\"severity\\\", \\\"location\\\", \\\"description